 you have problems with keeping your lines short enough with<br />8-characters indents, you should probably start looking for another career<br />than programming. Essentially, I think that people that can't keep their<br />indentation levels down to a maximum of three are simply not good<br />programmers. <br /><br />&gt; Printing the Source with current excessive indentation is quite <br />&gt; hopeless.<br />&gt; Apparently the Great White Leader uses _only_ X with _wide_ window <br />&gt; and has access to fine wide lineprinters.<br /><br />The Great White Leader (but call me "bwana" for short), feels that 80x25<br />characters is entirely possible. He doesn't want to use such devices himself,<br />but hey, even back when he _did_ use those kinds of resolutions he used<br />8-character indents. <br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
